  "bio": [
    "My commercial perspective didn't start in a boardroom; it started in community outreach, where I targeted stakeholders and built relationships to facilitate access to care for indigent youth in Alabama. That foundation in relationship-building evolved into a focus on systematic performance when I became a Continuous Improvement Manager.",
    "There, I learned the mechanics of continuous improvement within a culture of sales enablement. By coaching to specific behaviors, we set a foundation that carried into my role as a Regional Sales Manager, where I supported business units and sales teams in establishing and cultivating their online presence.",
    "Throughout every managerial role, one principle remained primary: managing businesses as metrics. Most consultants optimize a single channel, but I look at the system those channels live inside.",
    "Ever wondered why leads vanish or revenue doesn't match expectations? It often comes down to hidden friction points in your customer journey. As a certified Project Management Professional (PMP), I bring the delivery discipline to uncover these revenue leaks, fix the system, and turn strategy into measurable outcomes."
  ],
